		<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	
	<tr>
		<th align="left"><a name="31"></a>W4 - How to Package and Pitch Your Game to Publishers</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Tuesday, May 21, 2002, 1:00 PM&nbsp;-&nbsp;3:00 PM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">Ever wonder what's really going through the mind 
of a publisher during a pitch? What are 
publishers looking for from a developer? How are 
they judging you, your company, and your game? 
Learn what publishers are seeking from potential 
development partners. Learn how to package 
yourself, pitch your game, and get a deal. 
Attendees will be exposed to the tools needed to 
promote themselves intelligently and to pitch, 
and ultimately sell their game to a publisher. 
Topics to be covered will include how to deliver 
presentations, how to anticipate and address 
publishers' concerns, how to read contracts, and 
what to expect down the road after a deal is 
struck.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Location:</b> 411 - Theater</td>
	</tr>
	
		
