		<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	
	<tr>
		<th align="left"><a name="32"></a>W5 - Global Game Trends 101: Learning from the World's Top Titles</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Tuesday, May 21, 2002, 1:00 PM&nbsp;-&nbsp;3:00 PM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">Many foreign titles that become hits on their own 
turf often jump oceans and influence game 
development here in the U.S. This session will 
take attendees on a tour of the most popular 
games in Europe and Asia and attempt to 
understand the secrets of their success. Session 
highlights will include an overview of game 
trends in a number of foreign markets, a look at 
specific games, and an assessment of how these 
games might influence future development here in 
the States.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Location:</b> 404AB</td>
