		<th align="left"><a name="33"></a>W6 - The Business of Persistent Worlds: Learn from the Pros</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Tuesday, May 21, 2002, 1:00 PM&nbsp;-&nbsp;3:00 PM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">What's required to create, sell, and support a 
massively multiplayer, persistent-world title? 
Hear from developers who are advancing this new 
genre and learn where some have succeeded and 
others have stumbled. Attendees will walk away 
from this session understanding the hard 
realities behind budgeting, building, and 
supporting a massively multiplayer persistent-
world game.</td>
