		<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	
	<tr>
		<th align="left"><a name="34"></a>W7 - Developing Content for Wireless Handsets: Making Big Ideas Work for the Small Screen</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Tuesday, May 21, 2002, 3:30 PM&nbsp;-&nbsp;5:30 PM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">Designing games for PDA and mobile-telephony 
handsets requires a brand-new way of thinking 
about gameplay, user interface, and fun. But even 
with their smaller screens and paltry processing 
power, cell phones and PDAs present today's 
developer with tremendous opportunities for 
creating innovative games. This session will 
teach attendees how to capture gamers' 
imaginations by incorporating elements of 
community, building opportunities for character 
development, and squeezing as much depth out of 
the mobile platforms’ smaller palette as 
possible.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Location:</b> 411 - Theater</td>
	</tr>
	
		
