		<table border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
	
	<tr>
		<th align="left"><a name="35"></a>W8 - Design-Document Workshop: Don't Start That Game Without One</th>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Tuesday, May 21, 2002, 3:30 PM&nbsp;-&nbsp;5:30 PM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">The first step in creating a game is the 
generation of a design document -- a blueprint 
that guides the entire team and gives structure 
to the multifaceted, complicated, and sometimes 
conflicting challenges inherent in game 
development and production. This workshop will 
give aspiring and committed developers an 
understanding of the importance of a design doc, 
guidance in how to create one, and tips on how to 
use the document to focus energy, conserve 
resources, and deal with challenges during the 
course of a game's development.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#eeeeee"><b>Location:</b> 404AB</td>
	</tr>
	
		
		<tr>
			<td bgcolor="#eeeeee">
